                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The handwriting tend to left-sloping; it appears very irregular due to the variations in ruling (the size of the columns and the space between lines often differs significantly: e.g., fols. 15ra, 23r, 28r, 35rb), changes of the pen nib (slender or broad nib: e.g. fol. 1vab), changes in letters' height and varying spaces between the letters.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
