                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#4v">Fol. 4v</locus>: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is crudely written and hardly legible because the ink has faded away.
Haftä [sic] Gäbrǝʾel with his father Wäldä Giworgis [sic] and his mother Wälättä Maryam are mentioned in the lower part of the note.
The upper part has been filled in by another secondary hand, in strong amaranth ink, with the names of Dagǝmawi Zä-Mänfäs Qǝddus and his wife ʿAmätä Dǝngǝl. Furthermore a tabot (church) called Śǝllase ʾAyga is mentioned. It is possible that the same hand wrote Additio 2 in Ms. AMM-001 and Additio 3 in Ms. AMM-004. Both Mss. were donated by Dagǝmawi Zä-Mänfäs Qǝddus.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The name(s) of the original donor(s), mentioned throughout the Ms., have been erased and partly replaced with other names in a different hand.&#xD;
- Omissiones written interlineally or in the margins: e.g., fols. 6ra, 16ra, 20r, 50ra.&#xD;
- Musical notation on fol. 45rb (?).&#xD;
- Corrections made in a secondary hand: e.g., fols. 6ra, 15ra, 45r, 52vb.&#xD;
- Most of the erasures marked with parallel lines: e.g., fols. 8ra, 23rb, 34vb, 37va. &#xD;
- Crude letters: fol. 4r.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
